    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>fennel seeds</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>gram flour</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in a large bowl</p><p>Add the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to loosen and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tawa-style marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into large pieces and add them to the <strong>tawa-style marinade</strong></p><p>Mix everything together until the chicken is fully coated</p><p>Preheat the oven to 190\u00b0C/ 170\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 5</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot add the <strong>marinated chicken</strong> and cook for 5 min on each side or until golden and crispy</p><p>Once done transfer the <strong>tawa-style chicken</strong> to a plate (this will go back in the pan again later) and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, dice the <strong>cucumber</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>radishes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Add the <strong>diced cucumber</strong>, <strong>radish quarters</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mint leaves</strong> (save a little for garnish!) to a bowl with the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chopped salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>remaining tomato paste</strong>, <strong>remaining chicken stock mix</strong> and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> with 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and add the <strong>remaining cumin </strong>and<strong> remaining coriander </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook for another 1-2 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>tawa-style chicken</strong> to the pan and mix everything together then cook for 2-3 min or until the curry sauce is really thick and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Indian</strong> <strong>tawa-style chicken curry</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rotis </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 2-3 min or until the bread is hot</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-tawa-style-chicken-curry-with-roti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Indian</strong> <strong>tawa-style chicken curry</strong> with the <strong>warmed roti</strong> and <strong>chopped salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining chopped mint</strong> over the curry</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
